Outro detection calculates incorrect silence duration

## Bug

Some songs are reported with extremely long outro silence although they contain music until the end.

### Example

Emerson, Lake & Palmer - Fanfare for the Common Man

Reported outro:
556.71 seconds

Actual result:
The song contains music almost until the end. There is no 9-minute silence.

### Possible cause

The current algorithm calculates:

outro = duration - last_silence_start

This may use a silence detected earlier in the song instead of verifying that the silence actually reaches the end of the file.

### Expected behavior

Only report outro silence if the detected silence starts near the end of the file and continues until the file ends.
